The paper proposes an indoor localization system based on received signal strength (RSS) from access points (APs). This falls under the category of networked and mobile systems (cs.NI). The system also involves constructing a fingerprint map, which can be considered a machine learning task (cs.LG). The use of ordered AP sequences and the selection of a subset of APs for localization can be seen as a control and optimization problem (cs.SY). Information theory (cs.IT) is also relevant in the context of analyzing the performance of the system. Finally, computer vision (cs.CV) may be relevant if the system involves processing visual information from cameras or other sensors.
